review_blob: As a czech citizen Ive never come across this beer except in the states.  That said, its a decent American rendition of the Czech Pilsner.
An excellent drink.  Its Chimay Grande Reserve without the heavy carbonation.  Furthermore, its small local production guarantees a quality product at every sitting.  Well Done.

You sick people!! 
When you were ranking this beer werent under strong influence? It is so fruity, it makes your stomach to twist. If you want to try it, go for it but you will be sorry. Imagine a bitter rasberry tonic on crack.  Not incredibly deScriptive, I know, but you get the point.  Stick with Raz Stoli and tonic.
An absolutely wonderful experience.  It starts out slightly hoppy and once it warms the roasted malts take charge.  Warning:  Not for the weak at heart.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: I would rather drink my own piss than having Budweiser again.
Bad news! The most herby thing I have ever drunk!
Bitter, bitter, bitter. Can not have more than one a month.
Poorly balanced, it is not smooth what so ever.  Lacking flavor, the beer leaves the drinker wishing for a glass of water.

Thans to Anhauser-Busch Corporation, Budvar had to change its original marketing name to Czechvar. It is the greatest beer that ever came from the Heart of Europe - Czech Republic. GO BUDVAR!!!!! If you wont like this, you wont like anything.
I would not drink this beer again if they paid me.
